<article data-history-node-id="158" role="article" about="/article/usaid-partnership-imo-state-water-and-sewerage-corporation-introduces-interswitch-payment" typeof="schema:Article" class="node mb-3 node--type-article node--promoted node--view-mode-full clearfix">
  <header>

          <span property="schema:name" content="USAID PARTNERSHIP WITH IMO STATE WATER AND SEWERAGE CORPORATION INTRODUCES INTERSWITCH PAYMENT GATEWAY SYSTEM" class="rdf-meta hidden"></span>
  <span property="schema:interactionCount" content="UserComments:0" class="rdf-meta hidden"></span>

  </header>
  <div class="node__content clearfix">

            <div property="schema:text" class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The 1st Management Staff Meeting 2022 of the Imo State Water and Sewerage Corporation held on the 4<sup>th</sup> January 2022 introduced a new system which will be used in the corporation.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The meeting was presided over by the MD/CEO Engr. Emeka Ugoanyawu <span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:8.0pt" xml:lang="EN-US"><span style="line-height:107%">FNSE FNIWE NPOM FOSHA KSJI</span></span> with the attendance of all Heads of Departments as well as a representative of INTERSWITCH Mr. Ainoje Ohio (Team Lead East)</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The meeting agenda centered around ways to improve the Corporation through dynamism and imploring new strategies and systems to help achieve corporation's goals and objectives.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">According to the MD/CEO ISWSC, this dynamism is what has brought about the introduction of <b>INTERSWITCH PAYMENT GATEWAY SYSTEM </b>to the Imo State Water and Sewerage Corporation by the USAID E-WASH. </span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Speaking from the perspective of Mr. Ainoje Ohio the Team Lead East of INTERSWITCH, he said Interswitch’s broad network and robust payments platform have been instrumental to the development of the Nigerian payments ecosystem and provide Interswitch with credibility to expand across Africa.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Today, Interswitch is a leading player with critical mass in Africa’s rapidly developing financial ecosystem and is active across the payments value chain, providing a full suite of omni-channel payment solutions.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The USAID contracted TAWOL TECHNOLOGIES who is also the consultant for the ERP and will now be using Interswitch payment gateway system through engaging the ERP.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The Interswitch payment gateway system will be used for Revenue collection and Improve Accounting for Imo State Water and Sewerage Corporation in line with the international best practices.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><b>There are 3 payment gateways which includes:</b></span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">1. Paydirect</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">2. POS</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">3. Quick Teller</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">In line with their strategies, a help portal will be created for the corporation, and POS machines will be provided. Customers will have to start paying their bills through these gateways and sensitization will be carried out to this effect.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Furthermore, through the Interswitch payment gateway system, our customers can pay through any commercial bank, and depending on the gateway of payment used, whether quick Teller or paydirect, charges will either be burn by the customer or the corporation respectively.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The system is an "App", and all you need to do is to download it.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Also note that trainings will be conducted for selected staff that will be handling the reporting system for the corporation as the ERP will also be updated to accommodate zones that have not been included in the ERP.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"> </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">The MD/CEO Engr Emeka Ugoanyawu <span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:8.0pt" xml:lang="EN-US"><span style="line-height:107%">FNSE FNIWE NPOM FOSHA KSJI</span></span> thanked His Excellency Distinguished Senator Hope Uzodimma who has been instrumental to the changes attributed to the Imo State Water and Sewerage Corporation, and his interest to reposition the WASH sector of Imo State.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">He also thanked our USAID E-WASH partners for their support at achieving all milestones thus far.</span></span></span></p>
</div>
